## General Guidelines

### Always Do:
- ✅ **Always increment version** when making content changes (no exceptions)
- ✅ **Update "Last Updated" date** in metadata when version changes
- ✅ **Update both locations** if version appears in multiple places (frontmatter + metadata)
- ✅ **Document version changes** in CHANGELOG.md for significant updates
- ✅ **Use consistent format** across all file types
- ✅ **Keep version numbers in metadata only** (never in filenames)
- ✅ **Use semantic versioning** (understand what major/minor/patch mean)

### Never Do:
- ❌ **Never skip version numbers** (e.g., don't jump from 1.0 to 1.2)
- ❌ **Never reuse version numbers** (once published, a version is permanent)
- ❌ **Never change content without incrementing version**
- ❌ **Never use inconsistent formats** (e.g., mixing X.Y and X.Y.Z in same file type)
- ❌ **Never forget to update timestamp** when incrementing version

